The paper deals with combinatorial and geometric properties of planar point sets, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of algorithms to compute the reflexivity and related quantities also suggests that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The study of combinatorial bounds and NP-completeness of related problems suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The use of logarithmic-approximation algorithms suggests that it could belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the study of convex chains and convex hulls suggests that it could belong to the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category, which deals with the study of strategic decision-making.
